      • onStopEditMode

        public void onStopEditMode(UiEvent event)
        This method is invoked for the action stop edit mode, typically labeled with revert. This means that the changes in the (sub) dialog are discarded and it is switched to the view mode. If the current dialog is modified a popup should ask the user to confirm if he really wants to discard his changes or likes to cancel the operation.
        Specified by:
        onStopEditMode in interface UiHandlerActionStopEdit
        Parameters:
